  • Method Details

    • NeighborsNodes

      ArrayList<AStNode> NeighborsNodes(boolean IsAccessible)
      This is used to acquire all cardinal neighbors of the node.
      Parameters:
      IsAccessible - Determines if the function should take into account a wall between the nodes or not. True means it will only return nodes that do not have a wall between this node and the targeted node.
      Returns:
      Returns an ArrayList of AStNodes dependant on IsAccessible.

    • NeighborsNodes

      ArrayList<AStNode> NeighborsNodes(boolean IsAccessible, ArrayList<AStNode> Evaluated)
      This is used to acquire all cardinal neighbors of a group of nodes.
      Parameters:
      IsAccessible - Determines if the function should take into account a wall between the nodes or not. True means it will only return nodes that do not have a wall between this node and the targeted node.
      Evaluated - Refers to the nodes of the group that have previously had their cardinal neighbors requested.
      Returns:
      Returns an ArrayList of AStNodes dependant on IsAccessible.

    • UpdateHeuristic

      void UpdateHeuristic(CellPosition EndGoal, float NewG)
      Is used to update a cells G and H values
      Parameters:
      EndGoal - Refers to the end target supplied by AstarSolver.FindPath(AStNode, AStNode)
      NewG - The new value of G, which equals the current nodes total covered distance + 1, where 1 is the distance from the current node to the node being updated

    • compareTo

      int compareTo(AStNode n)
      Is used to compare the F and H values of the node.
      Parameters:
      n - Node in which to compare too.
      Returns:
      Returns -1 to 1, where -1 means the compared node is a better option than the current node, and the opposing for 1
